     NNNNOOOOTTTTEEEESSSS
	  The source file _m_i_n_i_r_b._c has been ruthlessly pruned (3k, 85
	  lines) to simplify uploading without benefit of an error
	  correcting file transfer protocol.  Do not reformat or add
	  tabs to the source file as this will complicate uploading.

	  _M_i_n_i_r_b uses the YMODEM header	file length information	to
	  avoid	storing	extraneous characters on Unix.	_M_i_n_i_r_b uses 8
	  bit checksum which may not be	compatible with	some programs
	  claiming to support YMODEM transfers.	 Please	read the
	  uploading suggestions	in the "_F_i_l_e _T_r_a_n_s_f_e_r _B_a_s_i_c_s"
	  (Reg.)chapter	of the Professional-YAM	or ZCOMM user's
	  manual.

	  _M_i_n_i_r_b does not remove any characters	from uploaded files.
	  The rz and sz	source files supplied by Omen Technology do
	  not contain extraneous characters that would affect Unix C
	  compilers.  Some PCDOS editors do add	extraneous characters;
	  It may be necessary to remove	these with a Unix editor such
	  as vi(1) or the undos(OMEN) program.

	  _M_i_n_i_r_b calls the Unix	stty(1)	utility	to set and reset raw
	  tty mode, avoiding sgtty/BSD/termio/POSIX incompatibilities.


